x4freetext: The separated-sector cyclotron
facility of iThemba labs
Fragments were measured with a telescope
consisting of an  active collimator followed by three
silicon detectors with thicknesses  of 50 mu-m,
150 mu-m, and 1 mm. The solid angle of the telescope
was 2.2 msr. Another 1-mm-thick detector vetoed
penetrating hydrogen  and  helium isotopes.
the statistical uncertainty.
The following systematic errors contribute to
the total  uncertainty:
uncertainty in target thicknesses
uncertainty in the incident flux
uncertainty in the solid angle, electronic
dead-time correction, and energy calibration
uncertainty in the emission angles
Data were received from Dr. H.Machner
